gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Wizards 117, Bucks 113
gameRecap.excerpt: The Wizards defeated the Bucks, 117-113. Corey Kispert (27 points, seven rebounds) and Deni Avdija (23 points, eight rebounds, five assists) combined for 50 points for the Wizards in the victory, while Giannis Antetokounmpo tallied 35 points, 15 rebounds and 10 assists for the Bucks in the losing effort, his 10th triple-double of the season, and 45th of his career. The Wizards snap a three-game losing streak as they improve to 15-61 on the season, while the Bucks fall to 47-28.
